{
 "name": "RPlog_Escape_and_Evasion_Training",
 "title": "Escape and Evasion Training",
 "summary": "Aboard the Star Destroyer Inquisitor, Marshal Krieg and Captain Keline Nelhrn convene the starfighter corps for the final stage of survival training, introducing the training officer Wolf and the SERE lecturer Lieutenant Vextin Mandor, who regales the pilots with a case study of evasion on hostile Sullust. The exercise then unfolds on Sullust itself: pilots Krieg and Liza Molokai are 'shot down' in the jungle and must evade pursuing stormtrooper squads under TK-3118 and TK-3120, led by ISB agents Dreven Mercurio and Dorian Navtilos, while a Navy rescue team aboard a shuttle (crewed by Keline, Sharid, Xy'lear, Wolf, and the sniper Arissa) races to extract them. A pitched simulated firefight erupts around the pilots' crevasse: Xy'lear is captured by Dorian, Wolf and Liza are stunned and hauled off by the troopers and Dreven, and the shuttle pours covering fire as Arissa picks off attackers. Forced to cut his losses, Krieg seals the hatch and lifts off, recovering some of his people while leaving captives behind, the shuttle finally breaking for orbit. The brutal evasion drill ends as a partial success, setting the stage for the ISB's own turn to hone their interrogation skills on the captured pilots.",
